The inspiration behind this video: 

Will Eleven get another chance at defeating Vecna? Is Max going to wake up? Can Will ever find peace in his life? These were just some of my biggest questions going into Stranger Things season 5, Volume 1. Seeing as it has been over three years since Stranger Things season 4's ending, my list of lingering questions has become overwhelmingly long. But I guess good things do come to those who wait, because Volume 1's four episodes quickly answer some of my most burning questions.

Set a year and a half after the events of season 4, Stranger Things season 5 finds Hawkins under military control following the "earthquake" that tore apart the town, which was actually caused by Vecna. The villain hasn't been seen since he was thrown from a window with a shotgun blast, but that hasn't stopped the group from staying ready for Vecna's next move. While Hopper and Joyce are helping Eleven train, Mike, Will, Dustin, Lucas, Nancy, Jonathan, Steve, and Robin coordinate ways to locate Vecna. Max is still present, but she remains in a coma, serving as a reminder about how high the stakes are.

Thank You So Much For Watching!
Stay Tuned! Stay Buzzed!

──────────────────

snippet.title: [Official Trailer] Dare you to death ไขคดีเป็น เห็นคดีตาย
snippet.description:
เมื่อชีวิตมีแค่ 2 ทางเลือก คือ TRUTH or DARE จะตอบความจริง หรือ กล้ารับคำท้า 
แล้วถ้าเป็นคุณล่ะ จะเลือกอะไร?
 การพบกันครั้งแรกของคนที่ต่างกันสุดขั้วอย่าง ‘ผู้กองเจษ’ (จุง อาเชน) และสารวัตรจบนอกอย่าง ‘คามิน’ (ดัง ณัฎฐ์ฐชัย) ที่ต้องมาแข่งกันตามหาว่า ใครคือฆาตกรตัวจริง ในคดีการตายปริศนา ที่ยิ่งสืบเท่าไหร่ก็ยิ่งมีคนตาย! แต่ในเรื่องร้ายๆ ก็ยังมีเรื่องรักๆ ให้หัวใจได้เต้นแรง 
 ร่วมกันพิสูจน์คดีของหัวใจได้ในซีรีส์ "Dare you to death ไขคดีเป็น เห็นคดีตาย" ทุกวันพฤหัสบดี เวลา 20:30 น. ทางช่อง GMM25 รับชมย้อนหลังทั่วโลกได้ทาง Netflix เวลา 21:30 น. เริ่ม 11 ธันวาคมนี้

กำกับซีรีส์ : เจตษ์ บุณโยประการ

รายชื่อนักแสดง
จุง อาเชน ไอย์ดึน           รับบท  ผู้กองเจษ
ดัง ณัฎฐ์ฐชัย บุญประเสริฐ  รับบท  สารวัตรคามิน
ชิม่อน วชิรวิชญ์ เรืองวิวรรธน์   รับบท  แชมป์
ซิง หฤษฎ์ ชีวการุณ    รับบท  พุฒิ
จูน วรรณวิมล เจนอัศวเมธี  รับบท  เชอรีน
โอม ฐิภากร ฐิตะฐาน   รับบท  เจย์
มาร์ค ณฐริศร์ วรกรเลิศสิทธิ์  รับบท  หมวดเคน
พร้อม ทีปกร ขวัญบุญ   รับบท  ไทม์
ฟลุ๊ค จีรัสณ์ วงศ์เพียร   รับบท  แทนคุณ
ป่าน ปทิตตา พรจำเริญรัตน์  รับบท  ปุยฝ้าย
แซมมี่ ซาแมนท่า เมลานี่ โค้ทส์ รับบท มิริน
อังเปา โอชิริส สุวรรณชีพ  รับบท  ต้าร์
อชิ พีระกานต์ เตียวสุวรรณ  รับบท  ต้นกล้า
เอิร์น ปรียาภัทย์ หล่อสุวรรณศิริ รับบท  เบล 
#DareYouToDeath

snippet.title: Sant, L7NNON, MC Marechal – MEIO
snippet.description:
Ouça em todas as plataformas: https://ads.somlivre.com.br/MEIO

Inscreva-se no canal e ative as notificações! #OQSHM

Letra – Sant, L7NNON
Vozes – Sant, L7NNON

Produção musical – MC Marechal
Captação – #VVAR
Mixagem & Masterização – Giancarlo Lino

Produção executiva – Upsla
Produção audiovisual – Thais Souza, Clara Almeida e Isabela Sabino
A&R – Lucas Pereira, Gisele Araújo e Rodrigo Vieira
Gravadora – Som Livre

Direção – Stameck
Assistente de Direção – J. P. Santos
Dir.Criativa / Prod. Executiva – Chico
Dir. de Produção/Prod. Executiva – Nanie Aguirre
Diretor de fotografia – Gb Santos
Assistente de Câmera – Gabriel Vitiello
Edição – Ariel Moraes
Color – Stameck
Direção de Arte – UZ1
Assistente de Arte – Madin
Contrarregra – KevynOContra
Elétrica – Lorran Barcelos
Assistência de Gaffer – Pedro Henrique
Captação Mobile – Vitória Dias
Designer Gráfico – Rafael Coelho/JOAO
Logger – Henrique Padilha
Maquiadora – Marisa Balbino
Styling – Núrya Boni

–

velho demais pros mais novos
o mais novo dos mais velhos
descobrindo pro que veio

sofro por coisas banais
sorrio de assuntos mais sérios

passeio entre gerações
sou tipo o filho do meio

sei reconhecer a pureza
até de quem tá na má intenção

são coisas frequentes no bairro
mas nem sempre dão atenção

também pudera, tanta urgência
mais fácil jogar corpo em valão

enquanto a vida segue o trilho
com sonho entalado num vagão

crianças falam sobre depressão
crescem sem rede de aceitação
pouco tempo pra entender quem são

adultos sem base perderam o chão
vão lidar só com a repetição
dos erros que eles já sofreram em vão

é um habitat cruel, ambiente hostil
um campo de centeio

por isso, eu não tenho medo
por isso que acerto em cheio

conheço a dor das esquinas
e desato o nó de quem grita em segredo
sou filho desse meio



observando o mundo ao Norte
numa viagem pra Oeste 
dentro do antigo 391

com a coragem do Sant e a gratidão do L 
e vendo o quê que elas tem em comum 

perto de casa e distante do ego 
vi tanto brilho e quase fiquei cego

o que separa os homem dos menino
é ver que correu tanto
e reconhece que ainda não tá perto 

sucesso não é ter dinheiro 
mas é preciso reconhecer
que ele ainda é um mal necessário

vencer não é só chegar em primeiro 
assim como nós não parabeniza
só em aniversário 

pare de ver o outro como adversário 
é que eu sempre percebo 
só que nem sempre eu falo 

veja 90% da cena e faça tudo ao contrário 
ou melhor, veja tudo acontecendo
e lembre dos que participaram

@JuliaVitóriaOfc apresenta Restaura o Teu Altar, quinto lançamento do DVD gravado Ao Vivo na Ópera de Arame - que conta com dez faixas, entre elas, Maravilhosa Graça, Canção dos Redimidos, com @NiveaSoaresOfficial, e os medleys João Viu / Além do Rio Azul e Amor Infinito / A Mensagem da Cruz.

Mais uma vez ao piano e acompanhada por um quarteto de cordas, a cantora gospel levantou o público, que, emocionado, declarava seu pertencimento e sua paixão por Jesus. “Foi um dos momentos mais tocantes para mim, ver todo mundo ali, cantando calorosamente, ainda mais por ser uma música inédita, isso mexeu muito comigo”, reforça Julia, que é muito conhecida por interpretar diversos louvores de adoração como De Dentro Pra Fora, Sem Palavras, com Luciano Camargo, Em Fervente Oração, Palavras, Mais Perto Quero Estar e Tudo Entregarei.

O DVD, registrado em 2025, conta ainda com a participação especial de @marcelomarkesoficial e @elisoares. Entre os sucessos de Julia Vitoria, além dos já mencionados, estão: Começo, Meio e Fim, Tuas Águas, com Gabriela Rocha, Ele Vem / A Cidade Santa, com Aline Barros, e Esperança, com Gabriel Guedes.
